# TypeScript Conventions

Project is **strict mode**. Avoid `any`. Prefer explicit, narrow types.

## Imports

```tsx
// ✅ Always use @/ alias
import { Button } from '@/components/ui';
import { apiRequest } from '@/services/api-client';
import type { PostResponseDto } from '@/dtos';

// ❌ Long relative paths
import { Button } from '../../../components/ui/Button';
```

Group: external → `@/` internal → relative (rare). Type-only imports use `import type`.

## DTOs / Types

- Backend request/response shapes live in `dtos/*.dto.ts` and are exported via `dtos/index.ts`
- Component props: define `interface XxxProps` colocated with the component
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions / utility types

```ts
// ✅
interface ButtonProps extends TouchableOpacityProps {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
  loading?: boolean;
}

// ❌ avoid
const Button = (props: any) => { ... }
```

## Async / Error Handling

```ts
// ✅ Surface meaningful errors; the api-client throws Error with message
try {
  const post = await postService.getById(id);
  setPost(post);
} catch (e) {
  console.error('[post] load failed', e);
  Alert.alert('Lỗi', e instanceof Error ? e.message : 'Không tải được bài viết');
}

// ❌ swallowing errors
try { await fetchData(); } catch {}
```

## Functional Components

ALWAYS functional components with hooks. Never class components.

```tsx
export function MyCard({ title }: { title: string }) {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);
  return <View>...</View>;
}
```

## Hooks Rules

- Custom hooks: `use-*.ts` in `/hooks` (kebab-case file, camelCase export)
- Don't call hooks conditionally
- Stable deps: memoize callbacks with `useCallback` only when passed to memoized children or used as effect deps

## Don'ts

- ❌ `any` (use `unknown` if truly unknown, then narrow)
- ❌ `// @ts-ignore` without a reason comment; prefer `// @ts-expect-error: <reason>`
- ❌ Default exports for components — use named exports (matches `components/ui/index.ts` re-exports)
